      • Serialization Methods

        • readObject

          private void readObject(ObjectInputStream in)
                 throws IOException
          Since this class should never be deserialized directly, this method should not be called. If it is, someone purposely created a serialization of this class to bypass that mechanism, so throw an exception.
          Throws:
          IOException

        • writeReplace

          private Object writeReplace()
          Implements the "write part" of the Serialization Proxy Pattern by creating a proxy which will be serialized instead of this instance.

      • Serialized Fields

          Optional<T> optional
          The wrapped Optional. Note that this field is transient so it will not be (de)serializd automatically.
